Its pretty simple Leetah...<br>
<br>
You need a large boiling cauldron (we down on the Gulf Coast here use a crawfish boiling rig usually) which you fill with oil.  The oil selected will directly affect flavor.  I've got friends who insist on peanut oil and others who insist on other types.<br>
<br>
Then you prepare the turkey (inject basting with secretive basting recipes, insert secretive seasonings into the skin  or other arcane practices).<br>
<br>
Then you lower the turkey into the cauldron of boiling oil - <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> carefully</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  It will spatter, splash, explode and other arcane actions as it is lowered in - be prepared for loss of flesh and or hair <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Cook for the appropriate amount of time for the size bird you are cooking.<br>
<br>
Typical permanent maiming mistakes for newbs:<br>
<br>
(1) not leaving enough room in the cauldron for the oil displaced by the immersion of the turkey.<br>
<br>
(2) insufficient splash protection<br>
<br>
